The widow of a retired police officer who shot dead two of their daughters before turning the gun on himself will receive $500,000 in death benefits despite earlier fears she'd be left penniless.

Former White Plains Officer Glen Hochman had filed new retirement papers removing his wife as beneficiary just 10 days before he carried out the killings in Harrison, New York on February 21.

It means that the state could recognize the original form - and it has indicated it will do so, the lawyer, Warren Roth, told the newspaper.

