Interviews with people who knew him found no one had an inkling that 'Mr. Hoffman would have committed this heinous crime,' said Harrison police Chief Anthony Marraccini last week.

Still, 'Harrison police investigators discovered a suicide note at the residence indicating that the killings were premeditated by Mr. Hochman,' he said. 

He added: 'It's difficult, especially when you see two young girls, their lives have been ripped away, brutally murdered. You can't get any rationale for that... The act is so incredibly bad.' 

